Step 1: Calculate the Debt to Equity Ratio.  
• Total Liabilities (taken from the balance sheet as Total Current Liabilities) = 3,054,996.05  
• Total Owner's Equity = 11,824,937.81  
• Debt to Equity Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Owner's Equity  
  = 3,054,996.05 / 11,824,937.81 ≈ 0.2583  
Rounded to two decimals, the ratio is ≈ 0.26.

Step 2: Calculate the Net Profit Margin.  
• Net Profit (from the income statement) = -1,175,062.19  
• Total Revenue = 7,099,920.95  
• Net Profit Margin = (Net Profit / Total Revenue) × 100%  
  = (-1,175,062.19 / 7,099,920.95) × 100% ≈ -16.56%

Step 3: Calculate the Operating Cash Flow to Current Liabilities Ratio.  
• Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities (from the cash flow statement) = -5,394,333.52  
• Total Current Liabilities = 3,054,996.05  
• Operating Cash Flow to Current Liabilities Ratio = Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities / Total Current Liabilities  
  = -5,394,333.52 / 3,054,996.05 ≈ -1.7656  
Rounded to two decimals, the ratio is ≈ -1.77.

Thus, the final answer in the required JSON format is:
{
  "solution": {
    "Debt to Equity Ratio": "0.26",
    "Net Profit Margin": "-16.56%",
    "operating cash flow to current liabilities ratio": "-1.77"
  }
}
